  <name>Speak-to-AI</name>
  <summary>Offline speech-to-text desktop app</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      A minimalist, privacy-focused desktop application for offline speech-to-text.
      Converts voice input directly into any active window (editors, browsers, IDEs, AI assistants)
      using the Whisper model locally for speech recognition.
    </p>
    <p>
      ðŸ“‹ For system tray integration on GNOME (install AppIndicator extension) and automatic typing on Wayland (setup ydotool),
      see <a href="https://github.com/AshBuk/speak-to-ai/blob/master/docs/Desktop_Environment_Support.md">Desktop Environment Support Guide</a>.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Portable: AppImage package</li>
      <li>Cross-platform support for X11 and Wayland</li>
      <li>Desktop Environment Support: Native integration with GNOME, KDE, and other Linux DEs</li>
      <li>Privacy-first: desktop, no data sent to external servers</li>
      <li>Support: multi-language, global hotkeys, automatic typing &amp; clipboard, system tray integration, visual notifications, WebSocket API (optional)</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
